      • findHabitats

        private java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> findHabitats​(Animal animal)
        Finds the habitats which the specified animal lives in. At first, it tries to find the habitats in the first paragraph of the page. If it is not successful, it tries to find a paragraph related to habitats. If still not successful, it looks for the habitats in the rest of the content.
        Parameters:
        animal - Specified animal
        Returns:
        List of all the detected locations for the specified animal

      • resolveWholeLocation

        private void resolveWholeLocation​(java.lang.String location,
                                  java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> locations)
        Adds all the sub-locations of the specified location to the list of locations already found. The sub-locations are west, north, east, south, central.
        Parameters:
        location - Location to be resolved
        locations - List of already found locations of a particular animal
